'''Heavy Isotope''' was a genre of [[Music/Legends|music]] popular among youths near the end of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]]. Generally played loudly, it was known to have a bass line reminiscent of one's own heartbeat. It originated in [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant's]] [[Slum district G17/Legends|Slum district G17]] from a vibrant youth culture, embodied by the band [[D.T. Spool and the Skroaches]]. It eventually became associated with [[Death stick/Legends|death stick]] culture in the [[Coruscant Underworld/Legends|Coruscant underworld]] in the years leading up to the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].<ref name="Slug">{{SW|url=news/slugthrowers-an-overview-of-popular-music-and-musicians-in-a-galaxy-far-far-away-part-1|series=Slugthrowers: An Overview of Popular Music and Musicians in a Galaxy Far, Far Away|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Heavy Isotope is almost certainly a play on [[Wikipedia:heavy metal|heavy metal]].

